{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = Professor | name = LeRoy Abrams | honorific_suffix = | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = October 1, 1874 | birth_place = | death_date = {{death-date and age|August 15, 1956|October 1, 1874}} | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Botanist]] | years_active = | employer = [[Stanford University]] | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = }}
'''LeRoy Abrams''' (October 1, 1874 – August 15, 1956) was an American [[botanist]] and author.<ref name="HUH">{{cite web | url = http://kiki.huh.harvard.edu/databases/botanist_search.php?mode=details&id=875 | title = LeRoy Abrams | work = Harvard University Herbaria – Index of Botanists | publisher = [[Harvard University]] | accessdate = 22 October 2015 }}</ref><ref name="Wilson">{{cite journal | last = Wilson | first = Albert | date = October 1956 | title = Wilson, Albert, 1903– Papers, ca. 1910–1995, Special Collections & University Archives M1397 | journal = Journal of the California Horticultural Society | volume = XVII | url = http://trees.stanford.edu/AW-abrams.htm }}</ref> He taught as a Professor at [[Stanford University]].<ref name="Wilson" /> He wrote and illustrated a four-volume ''Illustrated Flora of the Pacific States'', the final volume of which was published posthumously.<ref name="Wilson" />
He and his wife had a home overlooking the Santa Clara Valley.<ref name="Wilson" /> Their only child, a daughter, predeceased him.<ref name="Wilson" />
{{botanist|Abrams|inline=yes}}
Abrams is commemorated in the [[Specific epithet (botany)|specific epithet]] ''abramsii''.<ref name="Eggli Newton 2004">{{cite book | last = Eggli | first = U. | last2 = Newton | first2 = L.E. | title = Etymological Dictionary of Succulent Plant Names | publisher = Springer Berlin Heidelberg | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-3-540-00489-9 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=u2n5vusQ1DEC&pg=PA1 | access-date = 20 September 2018 | page = 1 }}</ref>
