{{refimprove|date=August 2011}} [[File:Eurovision all cities.svg|thumb|400px|Host countries and host cities of [[Eurovision Song Contest]] {{Columns |col1={{legend|#4d9221|A single contest}} |col2={{legend|#c51b7d|Multiple contests}} }}]] This page is a '''list of cities and venues that have hosted the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]''', one or more times. Future venues are shown in ''italics''. Since [[Eurovision Song Contest 1958|1958]], the host city has customarily been in the winner country of the previous year. [[Eurovision Song Contest#Host country|There have been exceptions]], however, when certain issues have prevented the winner from hosting the following year's contest. Hosting then passed to the country that had come second, or to another country that agreed to host. Such events occurred in [[Eurovision Song Contest 1960|1960]], [[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]], [[Eurovision Song Contest 1972|1972]], [[Eurovision Song Contest 1974|1974]] and [[Eurovision Song Contest 1980|1980]].<ref>[http://www.eurovision.tv/page/history#By_year The history of the Eurovision Song Contest - By year] Official Eurovision Website History. Accessed May 2012</ref>
With 6 contests, [[Dublin]] is the city that has hosted the most frequently. It is followed by [[London]] and [[Luxembourg_(city)|Luxembourg]] (4 contests each), and [[Copenhagen]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dr.dk/event/melodigrandprix/koebenhavn-bliver-vaert-internationalt-melodi-grand-prix|title=København bliver vært for internationalt Melodi Grand Prix|work=DR|access-date=2017-05-08|language=da}}</ref> and [[Stockholm]] (3 contests each).
[[Croatia]] is the only country to have hosted the contest, without winning directly.
[[Image:BBC Television Centre.JPG|thumb|150px|[[BBC Television Centre]] in [[London]] hosted the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963 Contest]].]] [[Image:Scandinavium entre 2005.jpg|thumb|150px|The [[Scandinavium]] in [[Gothenburg]]: venue for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1985|1985 Contest]].]] [[Image:Cinecitta studios rome italy entrance.jpg|thumb|150px|The film studios at [[Cinecittà]] in [[Rome]] played host to the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1991|1991 Contest]].]] [[Image:Oslo Spektrum.jpg|thumb|150px|[[Oslo Spektrum]] was the venue for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1996|1996 Contest]].]] [[Image:Athens Olympic Indoor Hall - exterior.jpg|thumb|150px|The [[O.A.C.A. Olympic Indoor Hall|Athens Olympic Indoor Hall]] in [[Athens]] hosted the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006 Contest]].]] [[Image:Belgrade Arena north.jpg|thumb|150px|The [[Belgrade Arena]] hosted the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008 Contest]].]] [[Image:Wiener Stadthalle Aussen 2008.jpg|thumb|150px|The [[Wiener Stadthalle]] hosted the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015 Contest]].]]
