on Song Contest 2019|2019]]'' |- |rowspan="8"| 2 |rowspan="2"| {{SUI}} | [[Lugano]] | [[Teatro Kursaal]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1956|1956]] |- | [[Lausanne]] | [[Palais de Beaulieu]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1989|1989]] |- |rowspan="2"|{{ITA}} | [[Naples]] | [[RAI|Sala di Concerto della RAI]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1965|1965]] |- | [[Rome]] | [[Cinecittà|Studio 15 di Cinecittà]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1991|1991]] |- |rowspan="2"| {{AUT}} |rowspan="2"| [[Vienna]] | [[Hofburg Imperial Palace]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1967|1967]] |- | [[Wiener Stadthalle]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015]] |- |rowspan="2"|{{UKR}} | rowspan="2"|[[Kyiv]] | [[Palace of Sports, Kiev|Palace of Sports]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005]] |- | [[International Exhibition Centre]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017|2017]] |- |rowspan="12"| 1 | [[File:Flag of Spain.svg|24px|border]] [[Spain]] | [[Madrid]] | [[Teatro Real]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1969|1969]] |- | {{BEL}} | [[Brussels]] | [[Heysel Park|Centenary Palace]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1987|1987]] |- | {{YUG}} ([[Croatia]]) | [[Zagreb]] | [[Vatroslav Lisinski Concert Hall]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 1990|1990]] |- | {{EST}} | [[Tallinn]] | [[Saku Suurhall]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2002|2002]] |- | {{LAT}} | [[Riga]] | [[Skonto Hall]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2003|2003]] |- | {{TUR}} | [[Istanbul]] | [[Abdi İpekçi Arena]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004]] |- | {{GRE}} | [[Athens]] | [[Olympic Indoor Hall]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006]] |- | {{FIN}} | [[Helsinki]] | [[Hartwall Areena|Hartwall Arena]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]] |- | {{SRB}} | [[Belgrade]] | [[Beogradska Arena|Belgrade Arena]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]] |- | {{RUS}} | [[Moscow]] | [[Olympic Stadium (Moscow arena)|Olympic Stadium]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009]] |- | {{AZE}} | [[Baku]] | [[Baku Crystal Hall]] | [[Eurovision Song Contest 2012|2012]] |- | {{POR}} | [[Lisbon]] | [[