'''Stephen Harrison''' (born 31 October 1960) is a British [[classicist]] and Professor of [[Latin Literature]] at [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford]]. He specialises in the [[poetry]] of [[Vergil]] and [[Horace]], the Roman novel and the [[Classical reception studies|reception of classical literature]].<ref>https://www.ccc.ox.ac.uk/Fellows-2/f/9/ Corpus Christi College. Retrieved 3 May 2018. </ref> Harrison has taught at the college since 1987 and is an occasional visiting professor at the [[University of Copenhagen]] and [[University of Trondheim|Trondheim]].<ref>https://www.classics.ox.ac.uk/people/professor-stephen-harrisonxx#tab-486916 [[Oxford University]]. Retrieved 3 May 2018</ref>
== Selected Publications == * ''Apuleius : A Latin Sophist'', Oxford University Press, 2000. * ''A Companion to Latin Literature'', ed. Blackwell, 2005. * ''Framing the Ass: Literary Form in Apuleius'' Metamorphoses, Oxford University Press 2013. * ''Horace:'' Odes 2, Cambridge University Press, 2017.
